Female genitalia (
Fig. 13
). Papilla analis triangular with obtuse apex, setose. Apophysis anterioris 2/3 length of apophysis posterioris. Lamella postvaginalis circular, emarginate posteriorly and setose laterally.Antrum cylindrical, posteriorly bulged with lateral processes, straight in middle, slightly dilated and narrowed to ductus bursae with a sclerotized arch basally. Ductus seminalis arising from posterior end of ductus bursae. Ductus bursae wrinkled, gradually narrowed with a coil near corpus bursae. Corpus bursae small, ovoid; signum absent.
